Looking at the parent class behavior, the issue is that when `this` vector has zero (default) values at certain positions, and we're doing element-by-element division with another vector, we should compute `0 / otherVector[i]` for all positions `i`.

The fix should ensure that all positions in the result vector are properly calculated by iterating through all possible indices.

